		{
			dependencies: ["19AC0B8C0B44FA30"]
			description: [
				"The Architectural Encyclopedia is a most interesting tome and a very popular one at that. It contains a vast array of knowledge about the architecture of the various civilizations of this world. For one who sees multiple ruins throughout their travels, this is quite useful to know the real names of these locations. Or at least, the attributed name."
				""
				"&a(This item mimics the /wits command, to display the name of the structure the player is located at.)"
			]
			id: "074421F47A443EC7"
			rewards: [{
				exclude_from_claim_all: true
				id: "54B70F6860297209"
				table_id: 1301202443783474816L
				type: "choice"
			}]
			subtitle: "Knowledge of Ruins"
			tasks: [{
				id: "3F478074FDC5FF2A"
				item: "tangiblecommands:wits_item"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 6.5d
			y: -5.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["19AC0B8C0B44FA30"]
			description: [
				"As one who travels a lot, it's often annoying to either have to setup somewhere and then pack up everything in the morning, or to sleep without shelter. Well, what about simply folding everything into a tent and packing it up?"
				""
				"These tent designs are frequently used by adventurers to serve as a semi-mobile base that is easy to pack and unpack. They can contain a lot more than mere sleeping bags. You can store whole beds, furnaces, even ample storage. They are quite heavy, but still a sufficient lazy solution."
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"&a(Shift-right click the tent to pick it up and its content in one go. "
				""
				"&aZip-up tents can be opened and closed with a right-click.)&r"
			]
			id: "4A8D37AE43828409"
			rewards: [{
				id: "708FB6090573ED28"
				item: "ironchest:iron_chest"
				type: "item"
			}]
			subtitle: "Nomadic Lifestyle"
